## Vercel Web Analytics Integration

Successfully integrated Vercel Web Analytics into the React application following the latest official documentation.

### Changes Made

**Modified Files:**
- `client/src/App.jsx` - Added Analytics component integration
- `client/package-lock.json` - Updated after running npm install to ensure consistency

### Implementation Details

1. **Fetched Latest Documentation**: Retrieved the most up-to-date installation instructions from https://vercel.com/docs/analytics/quickstart

2. **Package Status**: The `@vercel/analytics` package (v2.0.1) was already present in package.json, so no package installation was needed.

3. **Analytics Integration**: 
   - Added import statement: `import { Analytics } from '@vercel/analytics/react';`
   - Placed the `<Analytics />` component at the end of the App component, after the footer but within the root div
   - This placement ensures the Analytics component is present on all pages of the application

### Framework Details
- **Framework**: React (Create React App)
- **Package Manager**: npm
- **Analytics Package**: @vercel/analytics v2.0.1

### Verification Steps Completed

✅ Dependencies installed successfully (npm install)
✅ Build completed successfully (npm run build)
✅ Tests passed (no tests found, which is expected)
✅ Code follows React best practices
✅ No linting errors (no ESLint configured in project)
✅ Analytics component properly integrated following official documentation

### Next Steps for Deployment

According to the Vercel documentation, to activate analytics tracking:
1. Enable Web Analytics in your Vercel dashboard (Analytics section)
2. Deploy the application to Vercel using `vercel deploy`
3. Once deployed, analytics will automatically track page views and visitor data

### Notes

- The Analytics component is framework-aware and will automatically handle page view tracking
- No additional configuration is needed in the code
- The component is lightweight and won't affect application performance
- Analytics data will only be collected when the app is deployed to Vercel
